<title>CHINA: HK listed H-shares surge on reorgainsation hopes.</title>
<headline>HK listed H-shares surge on reorgainsation hopes.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-07-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>H-shares, the counters of China-incorporated firms listed in Hong Kong, surged on Wednesday on hopes the companies will benefit from the possible reorganisation of their mainland parents, brokers said.</p>
<p>&quot;H-shares have lagged behind the recent market rise and are being boosted by restructuring hopes,&quot; said Stanley Ng, research manager at Mansion House Research.</p>
<p>The Hang Seng Chinese Enterprises Index was up 17 points, or 1.64 percent, to 1,083 after retreating from an early high of 1,107.</p>
<p>Tsingtao Brewery rose HK$1.275 to HK$5.25 and Guangzhou Shipyard added HK$0.21 to HK$1.76.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong newsroom (852) 2843 6369</p>
